ackup/data-extraction XM...\",\n184:         \"HarmonyOS exposes the launcher EntryAbility through module skills, then continues startup into named in-app routes through the focused route registry and bootstrap page dispatcher instead of Android intent navigation.\",\n185:         \"HarmonyOS entry module keeps requestPermissions empty because the source manifest does not request runtime permissions in this batch scope.\",\n186:         \"HarmonyOS replaces Navigation Compose with explicit route ids and shell logic in app_router.cj and bootstrap_page.cj.\",\n187:         \"HarmonyOS replaces those Android version-catalog lifecycle dependencies with stage-mode build profiles, cjpm package wiring, and registered EntryAbility/FoodikeAbilityStage entry components.\",\n188:         \"HarmonyOS replaces those library pins with EntryAbility lifecycle hooks and the FoodikeBootstrap page registration path.\",\n189:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the DataStore dependency with LoginPreferencesService built on ArkData Preferences for persisted login/configuration state.\",\n190:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Gradle wrapper with build-profile.json5, entry/build-profile.json5, and entry/cjpm.toml as the active build pipeline for the registered EntryAbility lifecycle entry.\"\n191:       ],\n192:       \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n193:         \"Replace broad endpoints with precise target functions, types, resources, or tests before closing the group.\"\n194:       ],\n195:       \"riskHints\": [\n196:         \"current evidence uses broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n197:       ],\n198:       \"matrixRows\": [\n199:         {\n200:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n201:           \"featureId\": \"app-build-gradle-kts-329cf39b55-002-runtime-permission-request-permission-re\",\n202:           \"featureName\": \"Runtime permission request, permission result handling, or protected API access.\",\n203:           \"sourcePath\": \"app/build.gradle.kts\",\n204:           \"i